==================================================================
Property catalog provenance (SPEC §3.9)
==================================================================

Phase 2's RAG corpus (30 templates under
crates/vergil-properties/templates/) is entirely Vergil-original
(Tier 2 per SPEC §3.9). No source is vendored verbatim from any
external repository.

Each template's manifest.yaml records its `provenance` block with:
  - tier: original
  - license: Apache-2.0
  - inspired_by: human-readable reference to the public pattern the
    template captures (EIP, audit checklist, OZ source file name, etc.)

The "inspired by" attributions are informational pointers; the
encodings are independent implementations of the underlying
mathematical / behavioral property. Per SPEC §3.9, mathematical
properties (sum-of-balances, monotonicity, conservation, etc.) are
not copyrightable. Specific implementations are. The Tier 2
templates implement the properties as new code.

Tier 1 (vendored permissively-licensed sources) and Tier 3
(reference-only links to GPL/AGPL/BUSL sources) are reserved for
future catalog expansion. As of Phase 2, no Tier 1 or Tier 3
templates are present in the corpus.
